#+TAGS: sys root op


* sudoedit
* Description
A way to set which files can be edited without specifying with editor can be used.
It allows files that require root priv to be altered as the user not as root.
This is done by copying the original file to /tmp and once this file has been modified it is copdied back to the original.

* Usage
> sudoedit <file>
